===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|writen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|writan|wrītan|to incise, engrave, write, draw, bestow by writing|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|wrītanan|to carve, write|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|wrey-|to rip, tear|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|wer-|to rip, tear|lang=en}}. Cognate with Dutch {{term|rijten||to rip, tear|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|nds|-}} {{term|riten||to tear, split|lang=nds}}, German {{term|reißen||to tear, rip|lang=de}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|rita||to draw, design, delineate, model|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|ríta||to cut, scratch, write|lang=is}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|ritzen||to carve, scratch|lang=de}}.

